===Etymology===
==={{acronym}}===
WTFO

(Military slang): What the Fuck, Over! (1970's) 

Could be credited to George Carlin "WTF" However he may have picked it up when he was a radar operator in the the United States Air Force.

Alternate 
WTFO What The Flip, Over? (polite form)
or Are you really that stupid.

Originated as slang in the U.S. Army in the Second World War. The first word is sometimes [[bowdlerize|Bowdlerized]] as ''Fouled''.


